# Quality Policy: Relaxed

Focus on correctness. Coverage is not enforced; warnings are informational.

## Rules

- Tests must pass
- Linting issues should be reviewed but are not blockers
- Type checking is optional or advisory
- No coverage minimum enforced
- Format code where practical

## Rationale

Appropriate for prototypes, proof-of-concept work, or early-stage projects
where iteration speed matters more than exhaustive quality gates.
